# Accessibility Testing with Playwright

Use `@axe-core/playwright` to run axe accessibility scans inside Playwright tests. Never roll custom accessibility checks.

## Installation

```bash
pnpm add -D @axe-core/playwright
```

## Basic Page Scan

```ts
import { test, expect } from '@playwright/test';
import AxeBuilder from '@axe-core/playwright';

test.describe('homepage', () => {
  test('should not have any automatically detectable accessibility issues', async ({ page }) => {
    await page.goto('/');

    const accessibilityScanResults = await new AxeBuilder({ page }).analyze();

    expect(accessibilityScanResults.violations).toEqual([]);
  });
});
```

## WCAG A/AA Compliance Scan

Constrain scans to WCAG A and AA success criteria only:

```ts
const accessibilityScanResults = await new AxeBuilder({ page })
  .withTags(['wcag2a', 'wcag2aa', 'wcag21a', 'wcag21aa'])
  .analyze();

expect(accessibilityScanResults.violations).toEqual([]);
```

## Shared Fixture (Preferred Pattern)

Create `tests/axe-test.ts` to share common configuration across all accessibility tests:

```ts
// tests/axe-test.ts
import { test as base } from '@playwright/test';
import AxeBuilder from '@axe-core/playwright';

type AxeFixture = { makeAxeBuilder: () => AxeBuilder };

export const test = base.extend<AxeFixture>({
  makeAxeBuilder: async ({ page }, use) => {
    const makeAxeBuilder = () =>
      new AxeBuilder({ page }).withTags(['wcag2a', 'wcag2aa', 'wcag21a', 'wcag21aa']);
    await use(makeAxeBuilder);
  },
});
export { expect } from '@playwright/test';
```

Then use it in test files:

```ts
import { test, expect } from './axe-test';

test('decks page accessibility', async ({ page, makeAxeBuilder }) => {
  await page.goto('/decks');

  const accessibilityScanResults = await makeAxeBuilder().analyze();

  expect(accessibilityScanResults.violations).toEqual([]);
});
```

## Handling Known Issues

Exclude a specific element (and its descendants) when a fix is pending:

```ts
const results = await new AxeBuilder({ page })
  .exclude('#element-with-known-issue')
  .analyze();
```

Disable a specific rule by ID:

```ts
const results = await new AxeBuilder({ page })
  .disableRules(['duplicate-id'])
  .analyze();
```

Use fingerprint snapshots (not full violation snapshots) to track known issues:

```ts
// ✅ GOOD — snapshot only the fingerprint
expect(violationFingerprints(results)).toMatchSnapshot();

function violationFingerprints(scanResults: Awaited<ReturnType<AxeBuilder['analyze']>>) {
  return JSON.stringify(
    scanResults.violations.map(v => ({
      rule: v.id,
      targets: v.nodes.map(n => n.target),
    })),
    null,
    2,
  );
}

// ❌ BAD — brittle, breaks on any HTML change
expect(results.violations).toMatchSnapshot();
```

## Rules

- Always import `AxeBuilder` from `@axe-core/playwright` — never write manual DOM checks
- Always scope scans to WCAG tags (`wcag2a`, `wcag2aa`, `wcag21a`, `wcag21aa`) unless intentionally broader
- Use the shared `makeAxeBuilder` fixture for any test file with more than one accessibility scan
- Always `waitFor()` dynamic content before calling `.analyze()`
- Use `.exclude()` or `.disableRules()` only for known issues with a comment explaining why
- Never snapshot the full `violations` array — use fingerprints instead
